{"title_page": "Barkly Australian Football League", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{refimprove|date=August 2014}}\n\n{{use Australian English|date=July 2016}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox sports league \n| title           = Barkly Australian Football League (BAFL)\n| logo            = \n| caption         = \n| sport           = Australian rules football\n| inaugural       = 1991\n| teams           = 7\n}}\nThe '''Barkly Australian Football League''' (BAFL) is an [[Australian rules football]] competition based in [[Tennant Creek]] in the [[Northern Territory]] of Australia. The competition began in 1991 with all games played at Purkiss Reserve, Tennant Creek. BAFL season games could be played at Elliott oval from 2020 onwards due to the recent upgrade to the oval in 2019.<ref>https://www.katherinetimes.com.au/story/5394185/new-oval-for-elliott/</ref>\n<ref>http://newsroom.nt.gov.au/mediaRelease/28717</ref>\n<ref>https://dtsc.nt.gov.au/news/2019/investing-in-remote-sporting-infrastructure-elliott-oval-upgrades-underway</ref>\n==Current clubs==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Club\n! Nickname\n! Location\n! Premierships\n! Runners Up\n|-\n| Sporties Spitfires Football Club\n| Spitfires\n| Sporties Club, [[Tennant Creek, Northern Territory|Tennant Creek]]\n| 14\n| 5\n|-\n| Janapurlalki Football Club\n| Eagles\n| [[Tennant Creek, Northern Territory|Tennant Creek]]\n| 7\n| 8\n|-\n| Elliott Football Club\n| Hawks\n| [[Elliott]]\n| 3\n| 9\n|-\n| Ali Curung Football Club\n| Kangaroos\n| [[Ali Curung]]\n| 1\n| 3\n|-\n| YDU Football Club\n| Demons\n| [[Tennant Creek, Northern Territory|Tennant Creek]]\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| Canteen Creek Blues Football Club\n| Blues\n| Canteen Creek\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| Barkly Work Camp\n| All Stars\n| Barkly Work Camp, Tennant Creek\n| 0\n| 1\n|}\n<ref>http://www.foxsportspulse.com/assoc_page.cgi?client=1-4008-0-364483-0</ref>\n<ref>http://ntfootball.tripod.com/