{"title_page": "New Zealand men's national water polo team", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox national water polo team\n| Name               = New Zealand\n| FINA code          = NZL\n| Nickname           = \n| Image              = Flag of New Zealand.svg\n| Image_size         = \n| Image_label        = \n| Association        = [[Swimming New Zealand]]\n| Confederation      = OSA\n| Coach              = [[Zoltan Boros]]\n| Asst coach         = Lionel Randall\n| Manager            = Quentin Quin\n| Captain            = [[No current captain]]\n| Most caps          = Lachlan Tijsen\n| Top scorer         = Lachlan Tijsen\n| Home venue         = National Aquatic Centre\n| FINA ranking       = \n| FINA ranking date  = \n| FINA highest       = \n| FINA highest year  = \n| FINA lowest        = \n| FINA lowest year   = \n| First game         = \n| Biggest win        = \n| Biggest defeat     = \n| Olympics apps      = \n| Olympics first     = \n| Olympics best      = \n| World champ apps   = 7\n| World champ first  = 1982\n| World champ best   = 15th place ([[Water polo at the 2007 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's tournament|2007]])\n| World league apps  = 8\n| World league first = 2008\n| World league best  = Preliminary round ([[2008 FINA Men's Water Polo World League|2008]])\n| Website            = www.waterpolo.org.nz\n}}\nThe '''New Zealand men's national water polo team''' is the representative for [[New Zealand]] in international men's [[water polo]].\n\nThe team placed 5th at the 2014 [[Commonwealth Water Polo Championships]] in Aberdeen, Scotland.\n\n==Results==\n===World Championship===\n*[[Water polo at the 1982 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Men's tournament|1982]] \u2013 16th place<ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\">{{cite web|title=HistoFINA \u2013 Water polo medalists and statistics \u2013 Download |url=https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/histofina_wp_2018_final_0.pdf |website=fina.org |publisher=[[FINA]] |date=September 2017 